Nature of the changes (summary)
-------------------------------
moode-nopi ports the moOde stack to run on Debian 13 (Trixie) x86_64 and, by
extension, Armbian Trixie arm64/armhf, while keeping behaviour byte-identical to
moOde on a Raspberry Pi. It is a *distribution fork*, not an architectural one:
there is a single codebase, kept rebaseable on upstream moOde.

  - install.sh — an additive installer that builds and configures the moOde
    stack on a running Debian/Armbian system (audio binaries built on-device for
    parity: mpd selective-resample, caps eqfa12p, CamillaDSP, pleezer, peppyalsa).
  - Runtime platform detection via isPi(); minimal, isPi()-guarded edits to
    upstream sources where a Pi assumption cannot be fixed from the installer.
    Such edits leave Raspberry Pi behaviour unchanged.
  - ALSA plugin-chain and system configuration under etc/ adapted for non-Pi
    hardware.
  - Added documentation: INSTALL.md, DEVELOPMENT.md, CLAUDE.md.

